textAfterTable: 5318 Dientzenhofer           Discovered 1985 Apr. 21 by A. Mrkos at Klet. Kryštof Dientzenhofer (1655-1722) and his son Kilián Ignác (1689-1751) were among the leading architects and builders in the Bohemian Baroque style. Their churches and monasteries in Prague as well as in the country are still a part of Czech scenery. The name was suggested by J. Ticha.
